Class Family

java.lang.Object
com.example.gymmembershipgui.Member
com.example.gymmembershipgui.Family
All Implemented Interfaces:
Comparable<Member>
Direct Known Subclasses:
Premium
public class Family extends Member
Family is defined by a number of guest passes and all Member attributes. A Family instance can retrieve the membership fee for a family membership, can use a guest pass, and check out a guest.
Author:
Mahfuza Rahman, Arunima Tripathy

    • Family

      public Family(String fname, String lname, String dob, String location)
      Creates an instance of Family with name, birthday, and location. Defines Family membership by adding guest passes.
      Parameters:
      fname - the first name of member buying a Family membership.
      lname - the last name of member buying a Family membership.
      dob - the DOB name of member buying a Family membership.
      location - the location that the member will exercise at.

    • Family

      public Family(String fname, String lname, String dob, String expire, String location)
      Creates an instance of Family with name, DOB, expiration and location. Defines Family membership by adding guest passes.
      Parameters:
      fname - the first name of member buying a Family membership.
      lname - the last name of member buying a Family membership.
      dob - the DOB name of member buying a Family membership.
      expire - the expiration date of the membership.
      location - the location that the member will exercise at.

    • membershipFee

      public double membershipFee()
      Calculates the membership fee. If the membership has expired, fee is the quarterly cost of membership. If the membership has not expired, fee is the quarterly cost and the one-time fee combined.
      Overrides:
